[There have thus far been no human deaths from this outbreak of
Hendra virus. I do not believe there have been any human deaths in New
South Wales (NSW). However this is the 2nd horse to die from the virus
in NSW. Wollongbar is very close to the border between NSW and
Queensland. The previous horse death was also in that area.

This article leaves me slightly confused. It seems there are 8 people
exposed in Queensland, and an additional 8 people at this site in NSW.
Therefore is the initial all clear test on those people from
Queensland or those from NSW?

Since Wollongbar is close to the border between NSW and Queensland,
is this possibly from the same infected flying foxes? They have a
range approximately 40-60 miles. - Mod.TG

